# ThreadSanitizer suppressions for the TSan lane (harness --memcheck tsan).
#
# RULE (CLAUDE.md "never weaken a check"): ONLY third-party-internal noise may live here.
# NEVER add a suppression for a race between two frames of OUR code -- our races get FIXED.
#
# glib eventfd wakeup: g_wakeup_signal()/g_wakeup_acknowledge() write/read an eventfd that
# glib itself created on another thread. The eventfd IS the synchronization primitive; TSan's
# fd-based happens-before tracking misattributes it as a data race on the fd's shadow cell
# ("#0 write <libtsan> #1 <libglib> ..."). Classic false positive; every Qt-on-glib app hits
# it. Suppressing by CALLING LIBRARY keeps any our-code-vs-our-code race fully reported.
called_from_lib:libglib-2.0.so
# Qt event-dispatcher internals on top of that same glib wakeup (QEventDispatcherGlib posting
# across threads); pure libQt6Core-internal accesses -- our frames never appear in these.
race:libQt6Core.so.6
